## Issue Details
- **ID:** PAN-253
- **Title:** Inject new tracker comments into work agent prompt on restart
- **URL:** https://github.com/eltmon/panopticon-cli/issues/253

## Description
## Problem

When an agent is restarted on a reopened issue, it reads `.planning/STATE.md`, sees "Implementation complete", and immediately signals done — because it has no awareness of tracker activity (comments, status changes) that occurred after STATE.md was last updated.

**Real example:** MIN-693 was marked Done by an agent that fixed symptoms but not the root cause. A Linear comment was added explaining the issue was reopened and what actually needs fixing. Clicking "Start Agent" would cause the agent to read STATE.md → see "complete" → immediately `pan work done` again, never seeing the reopening comment.

Currently the work agent prompt only reads local files (STATE.md, `.planning/feedback/`, beads). It has zero visibility into tracker state.

## Solution

When building the work agent prompt, fetch the issue's recent tracker activity and inject any comments/status changes that occurred **after** STATE.md's last modified time.

### Implementation

1. **In `buildWorkAgentPrompt()` or the start-agent endpoint** (`src/dashboard/server/index.ts` ~line 8072):
   - Get STATE.md's `mtime` (or `0` if no STATE.md)
   - Call `tracker.getComments(issueId)` — already exists in the tracker abstraction (`src/lib/tracker/interface.ts:156`)
   - Call `tracker.getIssue(issueId)` to get current status
   - Filter comments where `createdAt > state.md mtime`
   - If the issue was reopened (status changed from Done/Closed back to open/in_progress), flag that explicitly

2. **Add a new template variable** `NEW_TRACKER_CONTEXT` to the prompt:
   ```markdown
   {{#if NEW_TRACKER_CONTEXT}}
   ## New Tracker Activity (Since Last Session)

   **IMPORTANT: The issue has new activity since your last session. Read carefully before checking completion status.**

   {{NEW_TRACKER_CONTEXT}}
   {{/if}}
   ```
   Place this BEFORE the "Check Completion Status FIRST" section so the agent sees it before fast-pathing to done.

3. **Include in the context**:
   - Current issue status (especially if reopened)
   - New comments with author and timestamp
   - Truncate very long comments to first ~500 chars to save tokens

### Tracker support

The `IssueTracker` interface already has:
- `getIssue(id)` → returns `state`, `title`, `description`
- `getComments(issueId)` → returns `Comment[]` with `body`, `author`, `createdAt`

Works for Linear (MIN-xxx), GitHub (PAN-xxx), and GitLab — all implement the same interface.

